## What to do
The B10 fix (commit b28087c) added a `ctx.Err()` check in the `err != nil` branch of Start() (line 126), but missed the `else` branch (line 133-136). When the server closes the connection cleanly (NormalClosure) simultaneously with context cancellation, `runOnce()` returns nil, the ctx/done select at lines 116-122 might not catch it (race between channels), and the else branch logs:

```go
slog.Warn("Tap connection closed unexpectedly, will reconnect", "backoff", backoff)
```

This is misleading during shutdown — the connection closed because we are shutting down, not "unexpectedly".

Fix: Add the same `ctx.Err()` check to the else branch:

```go
if err != nil {
    if ctx.Err() != nil {
        return ctx.Err()
    }
    slog.Warn("Tap connection lost, will reconnect",
        "error", err,
        "backoff", backoff,
    )
} else {
    if ctx.Err() != nil {
        return ctx.Err()
    }
    slog.Warn("Tap connection closed unexpectedly, will reconnect",
        "backoff", backoff,
    )
}
```

Or refactor to check ctx.Err() once before the if/else:

```go
// If context was cancelled, this is a graceful shutdown — do not log.
